# Brainstorm: Incorporating openresponses-gw Features into Antwort

**Date**: 2026-03-02
**Participants**: Roland Huss (antwort), inspired by Seb Han's openresponses-gw
**Goal**: Identify features from openresponses-gw worth adopting in antwort, prioritize them, and outline integration approaches.

---

## 1. Context

**Antwort** is a production-grade OpenResponses API implementation (33 specs, SDD methodology, Kubernetes-native, multi-tenant, zero-dependency Go core).

**openresponses-gw** (by Sebastien Han) is a focused stateful gateway for the Open Responses API, adding persistence, tool execution, vector stores, file management, and web search on top of inference backends.

Both projects are Go implementations targeting the same specification. This brainstorm captures features from openresponses-gw that could strengthen antwort through inspiration and selective reuse.

---

## 2. Feature Comparison Matrix

| Feature Area | antwort | openresponses-gw | Gap Assessment |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Storage backends** | PostgreSQL, in-memory | PostgreSQL, SQLite, in-memory | SQLite missing |
| **Vector store backends** | Qdrant only | Milvus, in-memory | Different backends, both limited |
| **Web search providers** | SearXNG only | Brave, Tavily | More provider options |
| **File management** | External ingestion assumed | Full Files API (upload, list, get, delete) + S3/filesystem backends | Significant gap |
| **Content extraction** | None | PDF, text, JSON, HTML, CSV extractors | Significant gap |
| **Annotations/citations** | Data model exists, no generation | url_citation, file_citation auto-generated | Generation logic missing |
| **Conversations API** | Implicit via response chains | Explicit CRUD + item management + pagination | Different approach |
| **Prompts API** | None | Template storage with {{variables}}, versioning | New capability |
| **Connectors API** | MCP client (spec 011) | MCP via Connectors API (register, list, delete) | Different management model |
| **Provider registry pattern** | Interface-based provider abstraction | Generic `Registry[T]` with factory/init() pattern | Architectural pattern difference |
| **Embedding service** | External (query-time only) | Configurable embedding endpoint + model | Similar approach |
| **Chunking** | External pipeline | Built-in chunker (fixed-size, overlap) | Missing for self-contained file search |
| **Multi-tenancy** | First-class, every layer | Not prominent | Antwort stronger |
| **Sandbox/code execution** | Kubernetes CRD-based, multi-runtime | None | Antwort unique |
| **Auth** | JWT/OIDC + API key | None mentioned | Antwort stronger |
| **Observability** | Prometheus + OpenTelemetry (GenAI conventions) | Basic | Antwort stronger |

